[SN]TITLE[SN]
Sawn-off shotgun found in Dundonald Cemetery

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A sawn-off shotgun has been discovered in a cemetery in east Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The weapon was found in Dundonald Cemetery on Saturday afternoon by a member of the public. It was taken away by police for further analysis.
Police said they were investigating where the weapon had come from and how long it had been there.
They appealed for anyone who saw suspicious activity in the area in recent days or weeks to contact them.
